<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-05T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="1807" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1807">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 767.70/90.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-05T19:00:00+02:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>All of the Powers save one have accepted mediation and the Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs believes that if mediation be made immediately it will
                            prevent the possibility of the violence and anarchy that would result in
                            case of a Turkish defeat and the disorderly entry of troops into the
                            city. He therefore requested me to ask you to instruct our
                            representatives at the capitals of the allied Powers in the interest of
                            humanity to urge cessation of hostilities immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>